    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Go Straight"
        },
        "text": "One of the most common directions is 'go straight'. In Levantine Arabic, you'll hear 'روح دغري'. 'روح' (rūḥ) is the imperative verb 'go', and 'دغري' (dighri) means straight.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "روح دغري",
            "english": "Go straight (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Rūḥ dighri"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "روحي دغري",
            "english": "Go straight (to a female)",
            "transliteration": "Rūḥi dighri"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Turn Right"
        },
        "text": "To say 'turn right', the verb 'لفّ' (liff) is used. It means to turn. Remember to differentiate between male and female forms for 'turn'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "لفّ يمين",
            "english": "Turn right (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Liff yamīn"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "لفّي يمين",
            "english": "Turn right (to a female)",
            "transliteration": "Liffi yamīn"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "يمين",
            "english": "Right",
            "transliteration": "Yamīn"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Turn Left"
        },
        "text": "Similar to 'turn right', for 'turn left' you use 'لفّ'. The word for 'left' has two common variations in Levantine: 'شمال' (shimāl) or 'يسار' (yasār). Both are understood.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "لفّ شمال",
            "english": "Turn left (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Liff shimāl"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "لفّي يسار",
            "english": "Turn left (to a female)",
            "transliteration": "Liffi yasār"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "شمال / يسار",
            "english": "Left",
            "transliteration": "Shimāl / Yasār"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
