    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Next To / Beside"
        },
        "text": "To describe the location of something relative to another, you can use 'جنب' (janb) which means 'next to' or 'beside'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "جنب البنك",
            "english": "Next to the bank",
            "transliteration": "Janb il-bank"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "المطعم جنب الصيدلية.",
            "english": "The restaurant is next to the pharmacy.",
            "transliteration": "Il-maṭʕam janb iṣ-ṣaydaliyye."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Opposite / Across From"
        },
        "text": "When something is directly across from another, use 'قبال' (iqbāl). This is a widely used term in Levantine Arabic.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "قبال المستشفى",
            "english": "Opposite the hospital",
            "transliteration": "Iqbāl il-mustashfa"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "البنك قبال المطعم.",
            "english": "The bank is opposite the restaurant.",
            "transliteration": "Il-bank iqbāl il-maṭʕam."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
