    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Following Instructions: 'Cross' / 'Pass'"
        },
        "text": "When given directions, you might hear verbs like 'اقطع' (iqṭaʕ) for 'cross' or 'مرق' (muroq) for 'pass by'. These are common imperatives.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "اقطع الشارع",
            "english": "Cross the street (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Iqṭaʕ ish-shāreʕ"
          },
          {
