            "english": "Cross the roundabout (to a female)",
            "transliteration": "Iqṭaʕi id-dawwār"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "مرق جنب الإشارة",
            "english": "Pass by the traffic light (to a male)",
            "transliteration": "Muroq janb il-ishāra"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Thanking Someone"
        },
        "text": "After receiving help, it's customary to thank the person. 'شكراً' is universal, but 'يعطيك العافية' is a very common and warm Levantine way to say 'thank you', literally meaning 'May He give you health'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "شكراً",
            "english": "Thank you",
            "transliteration": "Shukran"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "يعطيكَ العافية",
